OL,3,CCould social media firms be forced to
OL,4,Cmake content less addictive for under-
OL,5,C16s?
OL,7,FWhat does the Bill propose?
OL,9,FA key part of the Bill is a call for
OL,10,Fthe age at which companies can get
OL,11,Fdata consent from children without
OL,12,Fparental permission to be raised from
OL,13,F13 to 16 to make smartphones less
OL,14,Faddictive.
OL,16,FThe idea is that raising the age of
OL,17,Finternet adulthood would protect under-
OL,18,F16s from addictive algorithms as their
OL,19,Fdata wouldn't be used to inform the
OL,20,Fcontent they consume.
